modules.description: This module implements session management for web applications using Cohttp, handling session creation, retrieval, and expiration through a customizable backend. It operates on session data stored in a backend module, using keys, values, and time-based expiration periods. Key operations include loading sessions from cookies, generating new sessions, updating session data, and clearing sessions, with concrete use cases like managing user authentication state across HTTP requests.

This module handles session management for web applications using Cohttp, providing functions to create, retrieve, and expire sessions via HTTP headers and cookies. It works with session identifiers and metadata, typically stored in memory or a persistent backend. Concrete use cases include user authentication tracking and maintaining state across HTTP requests in a stateless environment.
